SUMMARY:The Simon & Garfunkel Story at American Music Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Now seen in 50 countries worldwide\, The Simon and Garfunkel Story is a critically acclaimed concert style theatre show about two young boys from Queens\, New York who went on to become the world’s most successful music duo of all time.  Using state of the art video projection\, incredible lighting\, and a full live band\, The Simon & Garfunkel Story is a moving and powerful concert featuring all the hits such as “Mrs. Robinson\,” “Bridge Over Troubled Water\,” “Homeward Bound\,” “Scarborough Fair\,” “The Boxer\,” “The Sound Of Silence\,” and many more. \nVIP 1&2: The Simon & Garfunkel Story VIP Experience  $172-$182 \nThe Simon & Garfunkel Story VIP Experience Includes: \n\nOne Ticket with in the first 10 rows\nA private 20-minute acoustic performance with the lead performers of The Simon & Garfunkel Story for VIP attendees only\, featuring exclusive Simon & Garfunkel songs not performed in the main show. “Stripped back\, with one guitar and two voices… singing in harmony.”\nA Meet & Greet and photo opportunity with the two lead performers of The Simon & Garfunkel Story.\nA limited edition\, collectible VIP laminate.\n\nVIP UPGRADE: The Simon & Garfunkel Story VIP Experience Upgrade $113 \nThe Simon & Garfunkel Story VIP Experience Upgrade* Includes: \n\nA private 20-minute acoustic performance with the lead performers of The Simon & Garfunkel Story for VIP attendees only\, featuring exclusive Simon & Garfunkel songs not performed in the main show. “Stripped back\, with one guitar and two voices… singing in harmony.”\nA Meet & Greet and photo opportunity with the two lead performers of The Simon & Garfunkel Story.\nA limited edition\, collectible VIP laminate.\n\n*Upgrade packages DO NOT INCLUDE TICKETS. A ticket is required to enter the venue. \n\nCome Explore Our Lancaster Theaters and the Arts\n\n\nLive Theater\nLive Entertainment\nLive Music\n\n\n\nDinner Theaters\nMurder Mysteries\nThings To Do\n\n\n\nArtisan Collectives\nArt Galleries\nEvents Calendar
